			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Twink?<a name="75556"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 19 05 10:04 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>re: mana, you won't need it at all till 39 (first song that uses it is the 39 charm) and you won't need it in quantity till the 60s.  Between 39 and  getting the AA fading memories in the 60s, I would worry more about mana regen (flowing thought) than the size of the manapool.
<br />

<br />
One thing not mentioned above is haste, if you're melee soloing get some haste, item haste stacks with your song haste.  (less important later when you have song-based ways to solo)
<br />

<br />
My personal list of priorities is:
<br />

<br />

<br />
Musical effects (to minimize instrument swapping; you will still want higher mod instruments for many uses, but it's nice to have minimal effects at all times) - I'm currently using epic 1.0 for this, so I am not prioritizing effects over HP, but I would if I didn't have epic or if I got to a level of play where items with 1.9+ mods were available
<br />

<br />
HP (STA also at the moment, since my bard is no where near the stamina cap)
<br />

<br />
FT (after lvl 39; at FT 5 and level 62 I can charm all day without losing mana, so that's enough for me at the moment)
<br />

<br />
CHA (mine is low enough that I don't really see any benefit from it though, so I should either bump it up in priority or give up and move it down)
<br />

<br />
Resists, especially magic  (Probably should be higher)
<br />

<br />
everything else</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
